eya_def_tools.data_models.eya_def.EyaDefDocument
IEC 61400-15-2 EYA DEF top-level data model.
Attributes: uri (Optional[Url]): Optional URI of the EYA DEF JSON document, which should have the field name '$id' in the JSON document. Default is None. schema_uri (Url): URI of the EYA DEF JSON Schema, which should have the field name '$schema' in the JSON document. It is assumed to be the latest published version if not included. Default is https://raw.githubusercontent.com/IEC-61400-15/eya_def/blob/main/iec_61400-15-2_eya_def.schema.json. uuid (Optional[UUID]): Optional UUID of the EYA DEF JSON document. Default is None. title (str): Title of the energy yield assessment (EYA) report. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the energy yield assessment (EYA) report, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the energy yield assessment (EYA) report, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. project_name (str): Name of the project under assessment. project_country (Alpha2CountryCode(StrEnum)): The ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 two-letter code of the country where the project under assessment is located. document_id (Optional[str]): Optional ID of the report document; not including the version when 'document_version' is used. This will typically follow the convention of the document management system of the issuing organisation(s). The field should not be empty if it is included. Default is None. document_version (Optional[str]): Optional version of the report document, also known as revision. As with the 'document_id', this will typically follow the document versioning convention of the document management system of the issuing organisation(s). The field should not be empty if it is included. Default is None. issue_date (date): Report issue date in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. contributors (list[ReportContributor]): List of report contributors (e.g. author and verifier) issuing_organisations (list[Organisation]): The organisation(s) issuing the report (e.g. consultant). receiving_organisations (Optional[list[Organisation]]): Optional specification of organisation(s) receiving the report (e.g. client), if relevant. Default is None. contract_reference (Optional[str]): Optional reference to contract between the issuing and receiving organisations that governs the energy yield assessment (EYA) report document, if relevant. The field should not be empty if it is included. Default is None. confidentiality_classification (Optional[str]): Optional confidentiality classification of the report document, if relevant. The field should not be empty if it is included. Default is None. epsg_srid (int): EPSG Spatial Reference System Identifier (SRID) for the Coordinate Reference System (CRS) used for all spatial data (e.g. turbine locations) in the EYA DEF JSON document. All location coordinates must be reported in the same CRS, which must be one that has an EPSG code. If different CRSs are used the data must be converted to be consistent with the EPSG code specified here. wind_farms (list[WindFarmConfiguration]): List of all wind farms considered in the EYA. This should comprise internal, external and future wind farms, including those used as reference wind farms in the wind resource assessment, if any. If different configurations are assessed for one or more internal and/or future wind farms in different scenarios, a wind farm object must be completed for each unique configuration, with the relevant configurations for each scenario referenced by wind farm ID. measurement_stations (Annotated[Optional[list[dict[str, Any]]], IEATask43WraDataModel]): List of measurement station metadata documents according to the IEA Wind Task 43 WRA Data Model, including all measurement stations relevant to the EYA, if any. It is recommended that one metadata document be completed for each measurement station, although the WRA Data Model allows for grouping multiple measurement stations into a single document. Default is None. reference_wind_farms (Optional[list[ReferenceWindFarm]]): List of metadata documents for the reference operational wind farms relevant to the EYA, if any. One metadata document shall be completed for each relevant reference operational wind farm. Default is None. reference_meteorological_datasets (Optional[list[Union[ReferenceMeteorologicalDataset, Annotated[list[dict[str, Any]], IEATask43WraDataModel]]]]): List of metadata documents for reference meteorological datasets used in the long-term prediction process of the EYA, which may include details of for example ground-based meteorological stations, reanalysis datasets and mesoscale model datasets used as long-termreferences. Default is None. wind_resource_assessments (list[WindResourceAssessment]): List of wind resource assessments, including results, at the measurement station locations. turbine_models (Annotated[Optional[list[dict[str, Any]]], IEC61400x16PowerCurveDataModel]): List of wind turbine model specifications. Default is None. scenarios (list[Scenario]): List of energy yield assessment scenarios.

eya_def_tools.data_models.eya_def_header.ReportContributor
Contributor to an energy yield assessment.
Attributes: name (str): Name of the contributor. email_address (Optional[EmailStr]): Optional email address of the contributor, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. contributor_type (ReportContributorType(StrEnum)): Type of contributor. contribution_comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments to clarify contribution, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. completion_date (Optional[date]): Optional contribution completion date (format YYYY-MM-DD). Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.general.Organisation
Basic metadata to describe an organisation.
This model is for example used for issuing and receiving organisations of an energy yield assessment.
Attributes: name (str): Entity name of the organisation. abbreviation (Optional[str]): Abbreviated name of the organisation. Default is None. address (Optional[str]): Address of the organisation. Default is None. contact_name (Optional[str]): Name(s) of contact person(s) in the organisation. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.reference_met_data.ReferenceMeteorologicalDataset
Metadata for a reference meteorological dataset.
The schema describes a dataset at a single horizontal spatial location. Separate data model instances need to be used to describe data at different location from the same source dataset (e.g. different grid cells from a reanalysis dataset).
Attributes: id (str): Unique ID for the reference meteorological dataset within the EYA DEF document. description (str): Description of the meteorological dataset. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the meteorological dataset, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. locations (list[Location]): The horizontal spatial location(s) of the meteorological data. Where a large number of locations have been used and it is not practical to include all, a subset can be included here and elaborated upon in the comments. time_resolution (TimeResolution): Time resolution of the reference meteorological data. data_period_start_date (date): Start of the data period in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. data_period_end_date (date): End of the data period in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD.

eya_def_tools.data_models.reference_wind_farm.ReferenceWindFarm
Reference wind farm.
Attributes: id (str): Unique ID for the reference wind farm within the EYA DEF document. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the reference wind farm, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the reference wind farm, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. wind_farm_id (str): The ID of the wind farm in the 'wind_farms' section of the top-level of the EYA DEF document, containing the configuration data for the reference wind farm. datasets (list[ReferenceWindFarmDataset]): List of metadata documents describing the operational datasets from the reference wind farm that were used in the EYA.

eya_def_tools.data_models.scenario.Scenario
Single unique energy yield assessment scenario.
Attributes: id (Optional[str]): Optional unique identifier of the scenario, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. label (str): Label of the scenario. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the scenario, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the scenario, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. is_main_scenario (Optional[bool]): Optional flag to specify whether or not it is the main scenario in the report. Default is None. operational_lifetime_length_years (float): Number of years of project operational lifetime. wind_farm_ids (list[str]): List of the IDs for all wind farms included in the scenario. Each ID refers to a wind farm configuration data object within the 'wind_farms' section of the top-level of the EYA DEF document. Only wind farms for which turbine interaction effects are modelled shall be included. turbine_wind_resource_assessment (TurbineWindResourceAssessment): Wind resource assessment at the turbine locations. energy_assessment (EnergyAssessment): Energy assessment details and results, including gross energy, plant performance, net energy and uncertainties.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_farm.WindFarmConfiguration
A collection of wind turbines considered as one unit (plant).
Attributes: id (str): Unique identifier of the wind farm. label (str): Label or name of the wind farm. abbreviation (Optional[str]): Optional abbreviated label of the wind farm. Default is None. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the wind farm, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the wind farm, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. turbines (list[TurbineConfiguration]): List of specifications for constituent turbines. relevance (WindFarmRelevance(StrEnum)): The relevance of the wind farm for the assessment ('internal', 'external' or 'future'). operational_lifetime_start_date (date): Operational lifetime start date of the wind farm in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. operational_lifetime_end_date (Optional[date]): Operational lifetime end date of the wind farm in the ISO 8601 standard format for a calendar date, i.e. YYYY-MM-DD. Default is None. installed_capacity (float): The maximum production (in MW) of the wind farm under typical conditions. If there are features in place to increase power output beyond the stated nameplate power of the turbines (e.g. so-called power boost solutions), the wind farm installed capacity should correspond to that increased power, insofar as it is reached under typical conditions and not only in rare exceptions. export_capacity (Optional[float]): Optional specification of the maximum permanently transmittable power (in MW) from the wind farm at the grid connection, or equivalent, if known. If not included it shall be assumed that the wind farm can transmit the full produced output. Default is None. restrictions (Optional[list[OperationalRestriction]]): List of operational restrictions at the wind farm level. Default is None.

eya_def_tools.data_models.wind_resource.WindResourceAssessment
Wind resource assessment at the measurement location(s).
Attributes: id (str): Unique ID of the wind resource assessment within the EYA DEF document. description (Optional[str]): Optional description of the wind resource assessment, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. comments (Optional[str]): Optional comments on the wind resource assessment, which should not be empty if the field is included. Default is None. results (WindResourceResults): Results of the wind resource assessment at the measurement location(s).
